node.text:
What does "well within" mean to you? 💛 The answer is different for everyone, but there is one common thread: it all starts with *connection* ...a connection to your mind, your body, your spirit, to each other.

So after a brief retreat hiatus, we're bringing everyone back together for something we've never done before. It's called Well Within. You just got to meet some of the speakers. As for the activities, you'll be able to choose from a menu of exciting breakout sessions and workshops:

✨  Guided meditations
✨  Yoga + movement classes
✨  Breathwork
✨  Sound bowl healings
✨  Kirtan (call and response chanting)
✨  Yoga nidra (meditative relaxation)
✨  Self-abhyanga (self-massage)
✨  Medical Vedic (eastern) astrology
✨  Somatic therapy
✨  Immersive Energy Healing
✨  Recapitulation exercises
✨  Musical healing performance and free-form movement
✨  Lessons from Deepak Chopra + other Mind-Body Health Experts
...and more!

Meet us on the California coast October 29-31 and find your wellness within. You can learn more at http://chopra.com/retreats/well-within

node.text:
A regular daily practice of controlled breathing is one of the best tools for vitality and longevity. 💛 The basis for breathwork originates in the science of yoga, specifically the fourth limb of yoga, known as pranayama, pronounced prah-nah-yam-ah or prah-nah-yam (both can be used).⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Although there are various definitions of the term, one interpretation is: *prana* (life force) and *ayama* (expansion), or expanding the life force using the breath. The ancient yogis learned that by controlling the breath, you can influence every aspect of your life.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Benefits of regular breathwork: ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
✔️ Reduced anxiety and depression⁠⁠
✔️ Lower/stabilized blood pressure⁠⁠
✔️ Increased energy levels⁠⁠
✔️ Improved immunity⁠⁠
✔️ Decreased feelings of stress and overwhelm⁠⁠
✔️ Reduction in PTSD symptoms⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Ready to develop your own pranayama ritual? Join @eddiestern in the Chopra App for his new series, "Breathwork for Balance " – link in bio.
